# Slot Card Redesign Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Re-architect the LCM slot card frontend to match the design captured in `docs/mockups/first-principles-v2.html`. The new card replaces the data-model-shaped sections (Primary Controls, Status, Conditions, Lock Status) with a journey-shaped layout: identity header (slot # kicker + state chip + name) → hero row (PIN + Enable) → collapsible Locks → Conditions (HA entity row + LCM overlay + helpers + Manage link) → click-through Activity row.

**Architecture:** HA-component-first composition. We delegate to native HA components wherever a sensible primitive exists (`ha-entity-picker`, `loadCardHelpers().createRowElement()`, `ha-relative-time`, `ha-switch`, `ha-icon-button`). We compose ourselves only where LCM-specific framing demands it: the state chip, the hero row layout, the LCM overlay strip on the condition entity, and the lock rows (sync status + code value have no HA-row equivalent). Each composed element is documented with rationale in the source.

**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Lit, vitest. The backend websocket payload (`conditions.condition_entity`, `conditions.condition_helpers`, `locks`, `last_used`, `event_entity_id`) is unchanged from the current shape — this is a frontend-only redesign.

**Prerequisite:** [`2026-05-01-remove-number-of-uses.md`](./2026-05-01-remove-number-of-uses.md) must be merged first. This plan assumes `conditions.number_of_uses` no longer exists in the websocket payload.

**Reference mockup:** `docs/mockups/first-principles-v2.html` — open in a browser to compare against during implementation.

---

## Composition Decisions

Documented up front so the implementor doesn't relitigate during each task.

### Use HA components

| Element | HA component | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Condition entity row | `loadCardHelpers().createRowElement({entity})` | Same primitive helpers already use; HA renders domain-appropriate UI (calendar shows event, schedule shows state, etc.) and provides more-info on click for free |
| Helper rows | `loadCardHelpers().createRowElement({entity})` | Already correct in current code; preserve |
| Manage Condition entity picker | `ha-entity-picker` (already used in `slot-card-editor.ts:219`) | Pattern proven in this codebase; gives users autocomplete, domain filter, friendly_name vs entity_id toggle |
| Enable toggle | `ha-switch` (already used) | Preserve |
| Eye / pencil icon buttons | `ha-icon-button` (already used) | Preserve |
| Relative timestamps | `ha-relative-time` (already used) | Preserve |
| Card chrome | `ha-card` (already used) | Preserve |
| Dialog chrome | `ha-dialog` + `ha-button` (already used) | Preserve |

### Compose ourselves (with explicit rationale)

| Element | Why we compose |
|---|---|
| State chip in header | No HA chip primitive that takes a tinted background + dot + text and lives in a card header. `state-badge` is the closest but is round, not pill-shaped. Tiny LCM-styled pill is the cleanest fit. |
| Hero row (PIN + Enable) | The 22px monospace PIN with eye toggle next to a label-aligned enable switch is LCM-specific glanceable framing. No HA primitive for "two prominent controls in a hero band". |
| LCM overlay strip on condition | Slot-specific framing ("Allowing access" / "Blocking access" + context like calendar event details). HA entity row says *what the entity is*; the overlay says *what it means for this slot*. Distinct semantic layer. |
| Lock rows | LCM-specific data: sync status icon, code value (can be revealed), last-synced relative time, sync action. None of this is in HA's lock entity row. |
| Event row at card bottom | Honest single-line "Last used: X · Yh ago →" that click-throughs to the event entity's HA more-info dialog (which has the actual history). Composing a single row is lighter than wrapping the event entity in a collapsible. |

---

## File Map

| File | Responsibility | Change scope |
|---|---|---|
| `ts/slot-card.styles.ts` | All slot-card-specific CSS | Major rewrite — new header/hero/event-row classes; delete unused `.lcm-section` wrappers, status section styles |
| `ts/shared-styles.ts` | Cross-card shared CSS | Minor — remove `.lcm-status-dot` if no longer used elsewhere |
| `ts/slot-card.ts` | Card render logic + state | Major rewrite of `_renderHeader`, `_renderPrimaryControls`, `_renderStatus`, `_renderConditionsSection`, `_renderConditionEntity`, `_renderLockStatusSection`, `_renderConditionDialog` |
| `ts/types.ts` | Type definitions | Minor — verify `SlotCardConditions` is correct post-Phase-1 |
| `ts/slot-card.test.ts` | Unit tests | Substantial update — new structure changes selectors |
| `ts/slot-card.integration.test.ts` | Integration tests | Substantial update — Manage Condition dialog flow changes |
| `ts/lock-codes-card.ts` | Lock codes card (separate component) | Audit only — may share styles |
| `docs/mockups/first-principles-v2.html` | Reference mockup | Read-only during implementation |

---

## Task 1: New header — slot kicker + state chip + name

**Files:**
- Modify: `ts/slot-card.ts:336-393` (`_renderHeader` method)
- Modify: `ts/slot-card.styles.ts:27-100` (header styles)
- Test: `ts/slot-card.test.ts`

The new header replaces the existing icon + title + pills layout with a two-row structure: a flex row with slot kicker on the left and state chip on the right, then the name as a 22px primary title underneath.

