- New header: `SLOT N · {entry title}` kicker (top-left), state chip (top-right), name as 22px primary title
- Hero row with always-visible PIN + Enable
- Conditions: HA entity row + LCM overlay strip + Manage link + helpers list
- Activity: single click-through event row at the bottom (replaces the speculative activity log)
- Manage Condition dialog: unified add/replace/remove with `ha-entity-picker`
- Status section removed (folded into header chip)
- Header pills removed (lock count → Locks summary; last_used → event row)

Reference mockup: `docs/mockups/first-principles-v2.html`

## Composition principles
- HA components first: `ha-entity-picker`, entity rows via `loadCardHelpers`, `ha-switch`, `ha-relative-time`, `ha-icon-button`
- Compose only where LCM-specific framing demands it: state chip, hero layout, LCM overlay, lock rows, event row

## Test plan
- [x] Frontend tests: `npm test`
- [x] TypeScript build: `npm run build`
- [x] Visual smoke test against mockup for Active / Inactive / Disabled
- [x] Manage Condition dialog: add / replace / remove flows
- [x] Event row click → HA more-info on event entity

🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)
EOF
)"
```

---

## Verification checklist (run before merging)

- [ ] Mockup `docs/mockups/first-principles-v2.html` matches the rendered card for all three states
- [ ] No `lcm-section`/`status-row`/`condition-item`/`empty-conditions` classes remain in `slot-card.styles.ts`
- [ ] No `_renderStatus`, `_renderPrimaryControls`, `_renderConditionEntity` (old version), `_getConditionStatusText`, `_getDomainLabel` methods remain in `slot-card.ts`
- [ ] `Manage Condition` dialog uses `ha-entity-picker` (not the custom datalist input)
- [ ] Event row dispatches `hass-more-info` for the event entity on click
- [ ] All `npm test` and `uv run pytest` pass
- [ ] `prek run --all-files` is clean

