{"body":"`_formatRelative()` uses `Math.round(ms / 86400000)`, which will report “in 1 day” for timestamps less than 24h away (e.g., ~23h rounds to 1). That contradicts the docstring claim that sub-day deltas collapse to “today”. Consider using an absolute-milliseconds threshold (e.g., `\u003c 86400000`) or `Math.floor`/`Math.ceil` depending on sign so anything under 1 day stays “today”.\n","line":620,"path":"ts/slot-card.ts"}
