{"body":"This now renders the activity row whenever `event_entity_id` is present, even if the event entity is missing from `hass.states`. The backend still includes `event_entity_id` when the entity doesn't currently exist, and `_get_last_used_info()` reports `(None, None)` in that case, so the card will show a clickable `Never used` row that opens more-info for a nonexistent entity. Please keep the old existence check (not just `state !== 'unavailable'`) before rendering or navigating.","commit_id":"b041bea028c64cd071d953f2c668d1020d49640f","line":322,"path":"ts/slot-card.ts"}
{"body":"`_getEntityRow()` caches and reuses a single HTMLElement per entity ID. Rendering that cached node again here means a helper that matches the main condition entity will be moved out of the condition block into the helpers list, because the same DOM element can't be mounted in two places at once. This needs a cloned/new row element per render site, or helpers should explicitly exclude the active condition entity.","commit_id":"b041bea028c64cd071d953f2c668d1020d49640f","line":649,"path":"ts/slot-card.ts"}
